    <abstract>
      <t>The Small Computer Systems Interface (SCSI) is a popular family of
protocols for communicating with I/O devices, especially storage
devices.
This memo describes a transport protocol for SCSI that operates on
top of TCP.
The SCSI/TCP protocol aims to be fully compliant with the require-
ments laid out in the SCSI Architecture Model - 2 [SAM2] document.</t>
